		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical History</head>
			<p>Harvey Jacobs was an American science fiction/fantasy author.  </p>
		</bioghist>
		
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>Spanning 1952 to 1994, the <emph render="bold">Harvey Jacobs Papers</emph> comprises manuscripts for published and unpublished short stories, screenplays and commercials, three novels and one short story collection.  In addition, there is a small amount of correspondence, memorabilia, and a brief description of the publishing history of his work, by Mr. Jacobs.</p><p>Arranged alphabetically by format, <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> (Boxes 1-3) includes manuscript and screenplay versions of <emph render="italic">Beautiful Soup</emph> (1993), and manuscripts and galley copies of <emph render="italic">The Egg of the Glak and Other Stories</emph> (1969), manuscripts of <emph render="italic">The Juror</emph> (1980) and <emph render="italic">Summer on a Mountain of Spices</emph> (1975) as well as manuscripts of a number of short stories.  Several include revisions.  </p>
		</scopecontent>
		
